==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Combatant
<hw>Com"bat*ant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>combattant</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who engages in combat. IN
military use, opposed to <contr>noncombatant</contr>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
mighty <xex>combatants</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A controversy which long survived the original
<qex>combatants</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Combater</ent>⟦br⟧
